<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>ACLEDA University Library</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.4.0/css/all.min.css">
    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
        }

        

        h1 {
            color: #2c3e50;
            padding: 30px 20px;
            text-align: center;
            font-size: clamp(1.8em, 5vw, 2.5em);
            border-bottom: 3px solid #2c3e50;
        }

        /* About Section */
        .about-section {
            padding: 40px 5px;
        }

            .about-section h2 {
                color: #2c3e50;
                font-size: clamp(1.5em, 4vw, 2em);
                margin-bottom: 20px;
            }

            .about-section p {
                color: #555;
                line-height: 1.8;
                margin-bottom: 15px;
                font-size: clamp(0.9em, 2.5vw, 1.1em);
            }

        /* Service Hours Section */
        .service-hours {
            padding: 40px 20px;
        }

            .service-hours h2 {
                color: #2c3e50;
                font-size: clamp(1.5em, 4vw, 2em);
                margin-bottom: 20px;
            }

            .service-hours ul {
                list-style: none;
                color: #555;
            }

                .service-hours ul li {
                    padding: 10px 0;
                    border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
                    font-size: clamp(0.9em, 2.5vw, 1.1em);
                }

                    .service-hours ul li i {
                        color: #2c3e50;
                        margin-right: 10px;
                    }

        /* Visit Us Section */
        .visit-section {
            padding: 40px 20px;
        }

        .visit-content {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
            gap: 30px;
            align-items: center;
        }

            .visit-content img {
                width: 100%;
                height: 400px;
                object-fit: cover;
                border-radius: 8px;
            }

        .visit-text h2 {
            color: #2c3e50;
            font-size: clamp(1.5em, 4vw, 2em);
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .visit-text p {
            color: #555;
            line-height: 1.8;
            font-size: clamp(0.9em, 2.5vw, 1.1em);
        }

        /* Responsive Design */
        @@media (max-width: 968px) {
            .visit-content {
                grid-template-columns: 1fr;
            }
        }

        @@media (max-width: 768px) {
           

            h1 {
                padding: 5px 10px;
            }

            .about-section,
            .service-hours,
            .visit-section {
                padding: 5px 10px;
            }

           
        }

        @@media (max-width: 480px) {
            .visit-content {
                gap: 20px;
            }

              

            .about-section,
            .service-hours,
            .visit-section {
                padding: 5px 10px;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <!-- About Section -->
        <div class="about-section">
            <h2>About US</h2>
            <p>ACLEDA University of Business has built a 28m x 29m library, 784 square meters in size, which can accommodate as many as 350 users at a time with high-quality standards, neat, clean, and quiet environment, fresh air, through light, wood-color tables, and seats; wide passage which is favorable for the disabled and pregnant women moving inside the library and also equipped with air-conditioners, ceiling fans, more than 2,000 titles, and more than 2,000 titles, 48% of books in Khmer and 62% in English languages which provide relevant information, focusing staffs and a benefit of Internet service and also IT equipment for service.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Service Hours -->
        <div class="service-hours">
            <h2>Service Hours</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><i class="fas fa-clock"></i>The library is daily open with the following hours:</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-calendar-week"></i>For Monday to Friday from 07:30 to 17:00</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-calendar-day"></i>For Saturday to Sunday Morning from 07:30 to 16:30. Except for national and international holidays.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Visit Us Section -->
        <div class="visit-section">
            <div class="visit-content">
                <div class="visit-text">
                    <h2>Visit Us</h2>
                    <p>At Stanford affiliates with a current and valid campus ID are invited to access the center whenever an area of Wallenberg Hall is available for roam use.</p>
                </div>
                <img src="/images/User/Contact/contact-3.png" alt="Library Visit">
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="visit-section">
            <div class="visit-content">
                <img src="/images/User/Contact/contact-2.png" alt="Library Leadership">
                <div class="visit-text">
                    <h2>LeaderShip</h2>
                    <p>Our mission is to encourage, stimulate, connect, and share. At Stanford Libraries, you will meet approachable, engaged, solution-oriented staff who are easy to talk.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="visit-section">
            <div class="visit-content">
                <div class="visit-text">
                    <h2>Support the Library</h2>
                    <p>Libraries value investing in research, preserving cultural heritage, advancing discovery using data, creating spaces that arouse curiosity, and believe in making information.</p>
                </div>
                <img src="/images/User/Contact/contact-1.png" alt="Library Support">
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>